INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `content`, `enabled`, `image_url`, `order`, `title`, `url_slug`, `created`, `modified`, `description`, `homepage`) VALUES ('63f8055a-749e-459c-95e4-905d46d47cd4', , 1, 'build/assets/images/posts/001-inspiring-your-workflow/post-image.jpg', 1, 'Inspiring your workflow', 'inspiring-your-workflow', '2019-09-04 19:43:13', '2019-09-04 19:43:13', 'To be Agile doesn’t only mean to do stand-up meetings every morning, to have retrospectives\r\nevery other week or to move cards in a Kanban board.\r\n<br><br>\r\nTo be Agile is a mindset, the kind of one that empowers individuals to pursue happiness through\r\nAgile values and teamwork. If you want to become a good Agilist the first thing you need to\r\nlearn is to forget about yourself. You don’t matter anymore, your team and your organization\r\nshould be the first of your priorities and you should be sure that, if you belong into a happy\r\nteam and a happy organization, you will be happy.', 1), ('ad119e56-ad74-4b60-9bc0-a19b8f9a5446', , 1, 'build/assets/images/posts/003-the-biggest-enemy-to-hyper-performance-teams-is-you/post-image.jpg', 3, 'The biggest enemy of hyper-performance is you', 'the-biggest-enemy-to-hyper-performance-teams-is-you', '2019-09-16 13:33:29', '2019-09-16 13:33:29', 'It isn’t an easy thing to admit. My team could be doing better. I could be doing better.\r\n<br>\r\nThere is even a magic quote that sometimes gives us space to look forward to the future but,\r\nother times is just an excuse to justify lack of commitment or even failure: “we assume each of\r\nus is doing the best she can do based on her current knowledge and circumstances”.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWe put a lot of effort in everything we do. We do what we firmly believe is the best that can be\r\ndone at any given moment. Is it enough in terms of effort? Is it enough in terms of smart work?\r\nAnd the answer, based on our current knowledge and circumstances, is probably yes, it is enough.', 0), ('d4960369-b437-4251-8cb1-86b24ac56de6', , 1, 'build/assets/images/posts/002-agile-to-be-or-not-to-be/post-image.jpg', 2, 'Agile, to be or not to be...', 'agile-to-be-or-not-to-be', '2019-09-16 13:31:52', '2019-09-16 13:31:57', 'I still remember the times of the Gantt diagrams. Maybe you never saw those but it was common in\r\nbig companies. A big project planned for years, with a couple of deadlines every 6 months or so\r\nand a lot of useless overwork and stress when the deadlines were close. Depending on how much\r\nthe manager did care about the project she started to demand this sooner or later but I never\r\nsaw it working out.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThen companies started moving into Agile methodologies implementing frameworks like Scrum or\r\nKanban. Sometimes because one team member had knowledge or experience with the framework, other\r\ntimes hiring expensive specialists like Scrum Masters or Agile Coaches.', 0);
COMMIT;

